observations.recommendation:
11. Create an appraisal/inventory committee to conduct actual physical inventory taking of all properties, plant and equipment and prepare annual Reports on Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE);
12. Direct the Accountant to make necessary adjustments on the records deficiencies noted in the course of inventory taking and in the reconciliation of the inventory report with the subsidiary ledgers;
13. After physical count and report of PPE’s are completed, prepare and maintain a subsidiary ledger card on each equipment, which should bear a Property Number;
14. The municipal accountant shall provide residual value in computing the depreciation and that fully depreciated property account shall be transferred to Other Assets account;
15. We also recommended to the Municipal Accountant or the concerned municipal officials to update the list of properties that needs to be insured and submit the same to GSIS. This guarantee that all properties were adequately covered by insurance in order to protect the interest of the government. For lost / damaged properties without covering insurance, liability therefore should devolve upon the parties responsible.

16. Advise the GAD Focal person to facilitate the formulation of GAD Plans and Budget (GPB);
17. Ensure that activities identified as GAD issues and concerns are properly addressed pursuant to the provisions under PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-01 and COA Circular 2014-001 dated March 18, 2014; and
18. Require Management to submit the Accomplishment Report on GAD Activities as required under the aforementioned regulations.

19. Strictly follow the rules and regulations set forth by COA Circular No. 2012-002 dated September 12, 2012 and COA Circular No. 2014-002 dated April 15, 2014;
20. Submit to this office the following documents: a) Local Disaster Risk Reduction Management Fund Investment Plan (LDRRMFIP); and
21. b) Report on Sources and Utilization of DRRMF;

1. We recommended that Management direct the Municipal Treasurer to record promptly all collections in the cashbook- Cash in Treasury;
3. Require the Municipal Accountant also record the collection to its revenue accounts pursuant to Section 13 of NGAS Manual for LGU, Volume I.
4. We also recommended that Management improve the system of recording of income and revenues to the agency’s books of accounts and its prompt deposits to the agency authorized depository bank and issuance of official receipts must be in numerical sequence or in chronological order in compliance with accounting system for collections.
